Mr. David A. Viniar served as the Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President of The Goldman Sachs Group Inc. from 1999 to January 31, 2013. Mr. Viniar served as the Head of the Operations, Technology, Finance & Services Division at Goldman Sachs Group Inc. since December 2002. From 1998 to 1999, he served as Deputy Chief Financial Officer of Goldman Sachs Group Inc and assumed responsibility of Goldman Sachs’s financing activities in the Treasury Department in 1992 and for the Controllers Department in 1994. Mr. Viniar served as Managing Director of The Goldman Sachs Group Inc. He has been a Director at Square, Inc since October 30, 2013. He has been a Director at The Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. since January 31, 2013. Prior to that, he was a member of the Structured Finance Department of the Investment Banking Division. Mr. Viniar joined in 1980 and became a partner in 1992. He was on the Union College Board of Trustees. He received an MBA from Harvard Business School in 1980 and a BA from Union College in 1976.



